<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 6:46AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Patchy Freezing Drizzle Possible This Morning...
Across portions of the southwest Adirondacks and Mohawk Valley,
patchy freezing drizzle will be possible through mid morning. The
best chance for freezing drizzle will be for higher terrain areas
above 1800 feet.
Motorists and pedestrians should be prepared to encounter locally
slippery ground surfaces this morning in these areas.</description>
